  "body": "The `bitflags!` macro generates a `struct` that holds a set of C-style bitmask flags. It is useful for creating typesafe wrappers for C APIs.\n\nFor example:\n\n``` rust\n#[feature(phase)];\n#[phase(syntax)] extern crate collections;\n\nbitflags!(Flags: u32 {\n    FlagA       = 0x00000001,\n    FlagB       = 0x00000010,\n    FlagC       = 0x00000100,\n    FlagABC     = FlagA.bits\n                | FlagB.bits\n                | FlagC.bits\n})\n\nfn main() {\n    let e1 = FlagA | FlagC;\n    let e2 = FlagB | FlagC;\n    assert!((e1 | e2) == FlagABC);   // union\n    assert!((e1 & e2) == FlagC);     // intersection\n    assert!((e1 - e2) == FlagA);     // set difference\n}\n```\n",
